    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="410"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d410">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5151/967</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Chief of the Financial Division</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Livesey</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Assistant Secretary of State</hi>
                        (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Berle</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-11">October 11,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Berle</hi>: These papers<note n="90" xml:id="d410fn90"
                        >See memoranda of October 6 and 7, <ref target="#pg_468">pp. 468</ref> and
                            <ref target="#pg_470">470</ref>.</note> show the present status of the
                    China Stabilization Agreement renewal with revision proposal, which has been
                    lost to sight for some weeks. Treasury proposes to stall indefinitely.<note
                        n="91" xml:id="d410fn91">Notation by Mr. Berle: “Unless you see some reason
                        to the contrary, FE’s memo seems sound.”</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
